profile:
ProHanging prides itself as being a high quality option for any household hanging service. Understanding the need to create a unique space means paying attention to detail and listening to the homeowner. Since 2006, ProHanging has been hanging Art, Mirrors, Picture Frames, TV's (TV installations), Blinds, and Specialty items in homes, condos and various institutions throughout the GTA.

You don't pay unless you are 100% satisfied with our service. That's a promise!

Art and Picture hanging is our specialty. We started our organization based on these services and continue to provide a top-notch customer satisfaction service at its finest terms.

We do not provide Electrical work.

Services Include: 

Mounting Service 
*Hanging artwork and sentimental pieces is more than just hammering a nail on the wall, it’s an Art on its own. We inspect all artwork to be safely hung on a particular wall, making sure that artwork will last a lifetime. 
*Mirrors Hanging and Installations 
*Decorative Items Installations
*Window Coverings 
*Blinds Hanging
*Bathroom Accessories Hanging
*Flat Screen TVs Mounting

Give us a call for a quote today and get it installed the right way.

Creative Interiors is a Toronto based design firm, specializing in custom decorating for residential & commercial clients.

Roz Pages’ background derives from the UK, once based in London, one of the top cities in the world for design. Having spent many working holidays in Europe, France & Italy being her favorite, she brings to Toronto a European flair which comes from her passion for fabrics & color. She is dedicated to creating exceptional, distinctive & uniquely personal Interiors.

Roz works with Realtors and has just staged a 5 Million Dollar house located by the Cricket Club.

All hired contractors are licensed and insured.

Hi, My name is Barbara. I'm thrilled to announce that I'm celebrating 18 years of Decorating & Designing.

Barbara Nyke Interiors & Design is a residential interior design & decorating studio.  We design custom kitchens, baths and décor for busy professionals primarily in: Toronto, North York, Etobicoke, Mississauga, Caledon, Vaughan, Richmond Hill, The Beach and Scarborough.  For projects located elsewhere, we are delighted to take our designs beyond the GTA.

Here's an article about "Why You Need to Hire a Kitchen Designer" - I'm the featured kitchen designer in the article.. Please copy & paste: https://blog.homestars.com/expert-opinion-why-need-kitchen-designer/

To get your project started, book a 2-hr kitchen design consultation with me.  I'll give you a comprehensive set of preliminary design recommendations including space planning, how to maximize counter space, cabinetry design, estimated project costs and more. Then we're ready for Step 2 of the NIKKA DESIGN process.

--------------

Barbara was a guest designer on "The Property Brothers" TV show.
 
I helped to redesign and renovate the entire main floor of a suburban 1960s home that included: the foyer, dining room, living room, kitchen and family room. Please see our Gallery for some photos.
 
"We design exceptional spaces. Our desire is to serve our valued and respected clientele by transforming how you live and work.  We rely on experience, expertise and impeccable integrity to complete projects on time, on budget and with stunning results".

CS STUDIO provides a unique and tailored interior design and decór services. Focused on residential projects and Boutique-style commercial spaces.

We are dedicated to making clients happy and satisfied by listening to their needs and collaborate with their ideas to offer multiples solutions for your design problems.

Carolina Segura is a certified Interior Decorator who began her career in interior design in 2015. Now she is a credited member of the field looking to collaborate and create a partnership with our clients and their homes.

profile:
After almost a century of activity, Dadashi Art Gallery™ is internationally known for high quality original oil paintings. With the largest focus on Canada, United States and Iran, we ship paintings to all corners of the world; we are crossing geo-political, cultural and religious borders and increasing communication through art.

The first Dadashi Art Gallery™ was opened in 1920 in Baku, Azerbaijan by Eman Dadashi and today, the Dadashi family operates three galleries in Tehran. Aby Dadashi, Eman’s grandson, established the first Dadashi Art Gallery™ in Toronto in 1989 and has since earned a reputation for his outstanding work and services within the Canadian art community.

Throughout its history, Dadashi Art Gallery™ has always been committed to three core values

1. Community – Contributing to society and demonstrating social responsibility by initiatives that impact lives outside the gallery.

2. Trust and Integrity – Representing ourselves with honesty and matching our behaviors to our words because we believe that long lasting relationships are grounded in trust.

3. Value – We earn our fee, not just collect it. We work hard on all our projects to find value through efficiency and creative execution and are committed to great products and service.

Initially offering only paintings, the gallery has expanded over the years to offer a wide range of products and services. Our collection now focuses on original pieces of classical paintings, decorative art, Persian rugs and carefully selected furniture. We also carry a selection of affordable artwork which allows access to art for all enthusiasts. Some of our most sought after services include art restoration, custom framing and private commissions.

We strive to ensure all our visitors feel welcomed to our gallery. Our knowledgeable staff often spends a considerable amount of time with clients to educate and narrow down the right piece for their space and budget. We work closely with the artists we represent and are enthusiastic about delivering art that makes you happy.

Open 7 days a week, we aim to create an accessible and inspirational art gallery for all. If you have any questions please feel free to call us on +1 416 250 6050 or reach us via email at info@dadashigallery.com.

Please visit us the next time you’re in the Greater Toronto Area!

profile:
How well does the art on your wall--or the absence of it--reflect your style and who you are?

Does it make a statement, or is it so unassuming that it practically goes unnoticed?

Are you renovating or are you a recent home buyer looking for the right ArtFit to finish your space or better yet--create a WOW factor?

If you'd like to see the walls in your home, condo or business come to life, then Annie DeMilo Urban-Artfitter would like to help. 


All images are gallery printed to provide the highest quality look and durability.

The firm imparts a bold, uncluttered design scheme to interiors which hold a timeless grace and elegance. We want you to enjoy the experience as much as you love the design.
